The paper deals with image super-resolution using deep learning methods, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of image priors and regularization techniques is also a key aspect of the paper, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the use of neural networks (cs.NE) and image processing (cs.MM) techniques.
